# Family Network ADK - Cursor Rules

## File Size Limits
- Maximum 150 lines per Python file
- Split large modules into focused sub-modules
- Each function should be under 30 lines

## Directory Structure
- Maximum 2 levels of nesting from project root
- Allowed: src/agents/, src/mcp/, tests/unit/
- Forbidden: src/agents/audio/processors/handlers/

## Code Organization
- One class per file for agents
- One MCP server per file
- Group related tools in single server (max 5 tools)

## Naming Conventions
- Files: snake_case.py
- Classes: PascalCase
- Functions: snake_case
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## Import Rules
- Absolute imports only
- No circular dependencies
- Group: stdlib, third-party, local

## Testing Requirements
- Each module must have corresponding test
- Test file mirrors source structure
- Run tests before committing

## Documentation
- Docstrings for all public functions
- Type hints required
- README per major component

## Dependencies
- Use `uv add package` only
- Pin versions in pyproject.toml
- No requirements.txt

## Forbidden Patterns
- No global mutable state
- No nested async callbacks > 2 levels
- No files > 250 lines
- No functions > 50 lines